{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8f01e14d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s1465b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1465b"},"text":"§ 1465b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Cuba Service","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Broadcasting Board of Governors shall establish within the International Broadcasting Bureau a Cuba Service (hereafter in this section referred to as the “Service”). The Service shall be responsible for all radio broadcasts to Cuba authorized by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1465a"},"text":"section 1465a of this title","children":[],"tail":". The Broadcasting Board of Governors shall appoint a head of the Service and shall employ such staff as the head of the Service may need to carry out his duties. The Cuba Service shall be administered separately from other Voice of America functions and the head of the Cuba Service shall report directly to the Board "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002061"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002061"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. There is no Board of the International Broadcasting Bureau."}],"tail":" of the International Broadcasting Bureau."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8f01e14e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/111/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–111, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-10-04"},"text":"Oct. 4, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/750"},"text":"97 Stat. 750","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tIII/s305/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title III, § 305(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 305(d)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/436"},"text":"108 Stat. 436","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dG"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. G","children":[],"tail":", subdiv. A, title XIII, §§ 1323(f)(1), 1324(3), (4), (6), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-779"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–779","children":[],"tail":", 2681–781.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8f01e14f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"prospectiveAmendment","id":"id8f01e150-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Repeal of Section","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section repealed upon transmittal of determination by President under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6063/c/3"},"text":"section 6063(c)(3) of this title","children":[],"tail":" that democratically elected government in Cuba is in power, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6037/c"},"text":"section 6037(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8f01e151-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id8f01e152-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Radio Broadcasting to Cuba Act which comprises this subchapter, and not as part of the United States Information and Educational Exchange Act of 1948 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id8f01e153-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1324/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 1324(6)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Board” for “Director” in last sentence."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1324/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 1324(4)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of this section by substituting “the International Broadcasting Bureau” for “the Voice of America”, was executed by making the substitution for text in two places to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1324/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 1324(3)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “the Broadcasting Board of Governors” for “the Director of the United States Information Agency” each place it appears, was executed by substituting “Broadcasting Board of Governors” for “Director of the United States Information Agency” in two places, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236","children":[],"tail":" substituted “of the Voice of America” for “and the Associate Director for Broadcasting of the United States Information Agency”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id8f01e154-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id8f01e155-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Broadcasting Board of Governors renamed United States Agency for Global Media pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6204/a/21"},"text":"section 6204(a)(21) of this title","children":[],"tail":". The renaming was effectuated by notice to congressional appropriations committees dated "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 2018","children":[],"tail":", and became effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-22"},"text":"Aug. 22, 2018","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id8f01e156-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1998 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1999","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1301"},"text":"section 1301 of Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6531"},"text":"section 6531 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8f01e157-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prohibitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/323/tVII/s703/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–323, title VII, § 703(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/1941"},"text":"130 Stat. 1941","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/94/s11"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–94, § 11","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/2040"},"text":"131 Stat. 2040","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/115/94/s11"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of law, any change to the Federal status of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Cuba Service established pursuant to section 4 of the Radio Broadcasting to Cuba Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1465b"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 1465b","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/111"},"text":"Public Law 98–111","children":[],"tail":") is prohibited unless such section is explicitly repealed and such service is dissolved by an Act of Congress enacted on or after the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2016","children":[],"tail":"]; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Television Marti Service established by section 244(a) of Television Broadcasting to Cuba Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1465cc"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 1465cc","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/246"},"text":"Public Law 101–246","children":[],"tail":") is prohibited unless such section is explicitly repealed and such service is dissolved by an Act of Congress enacted on or after the date of the enactment of this Act."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definition","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In this subsection, the term ‘change to the Federal status’, with respect to a service referred to in subparagraph (A) or (B) of paragraph (1), includes privatization, subordination to a private or private-public entity, or merger with a private or public-private entity of such service.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
